Vice President Joe Biden released a statement on the passing of Elie Wiesel, a Holocaust survivor and author of the book "Night." Biden expressed his gratitude for the opportunity to know Wiesel and learn from him. He emphasized the importance of educating future generations about the Holocaust and never forgetting its horrors. Biden also praised Wiesel's belief in the resilience of the human spirit and his commitment to living with purpose and kindness. The Vice President acknowledged Wiesel's lifelong fight for what he believed was right and expressed his condolences to Wiesel's family.